In matters such as these which, regrettably, can carry such weight as to tip the balance towards war or peace, exploitation for political ends is unacceptable; 
          however
        , equally unacceptable are superficial expressions which, I am sad to say, appear to mask attitudes of intolerance which must be opposed.

I wish we could take this document to the Conciliation Committee; 
          then
        , Mr de Roo, we would get away from your rather exaggerated demands and arrive at realistic ones that would get us somewhere in the overall scheme of things.
